Message.Title: Corr. vector warning
Message.Description: Sensor correction vector calculations failed due to previous error.

Message.Title: Corr. vector warning
Message.Description: Sensor correction vector calculations failed due to previous error.

Message.Title: Non optimal movement
Message.Description: Required torque too high. Manual adjustment of weave frequency or amplitude is needed.
Message.Actions: Reduce weave frequency or weave amplitude in this movement. Alternatively, reduce speed.

Message.Title: Relay signal not found
Message.Description: The signal for relay is not found in the I/O configuration. The mechanical unit using this relay is ignored.
Message.Actions: Check I/O signal definitions and System Parameters definition in topic Motion, Type: Relay.

Message.Title: Permanent interpolator lock error
Message.Description: Scanned number of active joints not equal to expected number of joints.
Message.Actions: Check configuration of the unit that is using general kinematics.

Message.Title: Too many TCP speed's
Message.Description: The number of TCP speed's in one segment is too large. Maximum number of TCP speed's is .
Message.Actions: Check if one segment has too many TCP speed's set or if a sequence of segments have increasing DipLag.

Message.Title: Jogging error
Message.Description: Jogging is started too soon after program stop.
Message.Actions: Try to jog the robot again.

Message.Title: Joint not synchronized
Message.Description: The speed of joint before power down/failure was too high.
Message.Actions: Make a new update of the revolution counter.

Message.Title: Internal position error
Message.Description: Error caused by internal numerical limitation. Joint number . Calculated reference position = .
Message.Actions:
- Adjust the system parameters in Uncal ctrl master 0.
- If TuneServo is used, adjust parameter Tune_df.

Message.Title: Cannot move independent
Message.Description: Joint cannot be moved in independent mode.
Message.Actions: Make sure that independent mode is not used when trying to move joint.

Message.Title: Calibration failed
Message.Description: Points 0 and 1 too close.
Message.Actions: Make a new calibration with larger distance between points 0 and 1.

Message.Title: Calibration failed
Message.Description: Points 0, 1, 2 on a line or point 2 too close to points 0 or 1.
Message.Actions: Make a new calibration with points moved so that 0, 1 and 2 are not on a line or with larger distance between point 2 and points 0 and 1.

Message.Title: Calibration failed
Message.Description: Internal error during calibration due to unknown origin switch.
Message.Actions:
- Report the occurrance to ABB.
- Make a new calibration.

Message.Title: Torque error
Message.Description: Torque calculation error due to high speed for mechanical unit . Internal info code
Message.Actions:
- Check load data.
- Reduce speed.

Message.Title: Orientation outside reach
Message.Description: The error of the programmed orientation exceeds the acceptance limit.
Message.Actions:
- Adjust robtarget orientation.
- Adjust/check orientations of currently used frames: tool frame, base frame, user frame, object frame.
- It is possible (but not recommendable) to switch off the orientation supervision using the corresponding system parameter. Please see system parameters documentation for details (Topic Motion/Type Robot).

Message.Title: Measurement node used
Message.Description: The measurement node for joint is already used.
Message.Actions: Select another node.

Message.Title: Motion supervision
Message.Description: Motion supervision triggered for axis on mechanical unit .
Message.Consequences: The movement of mechanical unit is halted immediately. It then returns to a position on the path on which it was running. There, it will remain in status Motors ON, awaiting a start request.
Message.Causes: Triggering of the motion supervision may be caused by a collision, incorrect load definition or forces in external process.
Message.Actions:
1) If possible, acknowledge the fault, and resume operation by pressing the Start button on the teach pendant.
2) Make sure any loads are defined and identified correctly.
3) If the mechanical unit is exposed to forces from the external processes, use RAPID command or system parameters to raise the supervision level.

Message.Title: Data logger error
Message.Actions: Solution:

Message.Title: Probe warning
Message.Description: Probe buffer is full.

Message.Title: Add intermediate point
Message.Description: Intermediate point not coordinated to external pos mechanical unit is necessary when changing conveyor.
Message.Actions: Create an intermediate point then change the conveyor.

Message.Title: Missing function
Message.Description: Friction compensation can not be activated for joint .
Message.Actions: Install the option Advanced Shape Tuning.

Message.Title: Kinematic limitation
Message.Description:
No acceptable solution found. Residual: deg in orientation, mm in x,
mm in y, mm in z.
Message.Actions: Insert an intermediary point. Check singularity. Increase position and orient. tolerance. Use MoveAbsJ. Check working range.

Message.Title: Load identification fail
Message.Description: Cannot perform load identification because configuration angle is too small.
Message.Actions: - Increase configuration angle.

Message.Title: Work area config failed
Message.Description: Possibly the defined work area is larger than max allowed area for robot .
Message.Actions: Adjust the work area parameters in Robot system parameters and try again.

Message.Title: Load identification fail
Message.Description: Axis will move outside working range.
Message.Actions: Move the axis to a position further from the working range limit.

Message.Title: Path not finished
Message.Description:
Task:
Previous motion path was not finished before new motion was sent.
Program Ref.
Message.Actions: Use StorePath when in Trap routines. Move the program pointer and start a new movement.

Message.Title: No input signal
Message.Description: No input signal to contactor relay for mechanical unit
Message.Actions: Ensure that an input signal is connected and configured.

Message.Title: Object outside limit
Message.Description: Object on conveyor is outside max dist or min dist limits. Object Dropped.
Message.Actions: Check limits or reduce conveyor speed.

Message.Title: Mismatch type - MechUnit
Message.Description: Mismatch between selected identification type and selected mechanical unit.
Message.Actions: Make sure that selected type corresponds to selected mechanical unit and try again.

Message.Title: Cannot define load
Message.Description: It is not allowed to define a load on axis for mechanical unit or the interpolation is not stopped in a finepoint.
Message.Actions: Change axis number, mechanical unit or change the move before to finepoint.

Message.Title: Old boot safe area lost
Message.Description:
Error in boot safe memory area.
- Area updated with new data.
- System unsynchronized.
Message.Actions: Update all revolution counters.

Message.Title: Motor reference error
Message.Description: Calculation time for motor references exceeds internal limits.
Message.Actions:
- Reduce load on main computer.
- Restart controller.

Message.Title: Test signal error
Message.Description: Invalid channel number .
Message.Actions: Allowed channel numbers are 1 - 12 for test signals and 1 - 6 for data log signals.

Message.Title: Test signal error
Message.Description: Unknown test signal number .
Message.Actions: Make sure that a valid test signal number is defined.

Message.Title: Test signal error
Message.Description: Unknown mechanical unit .
Message.Actions: Check spelling or configuration.

Message.Title: Test signal error
Message.Description: Invalid axis number for mechanical unit .
Message.Actions: Check mechanical unit and axis number.

Message.Title: Test signal error
Message.Description: Mechanical unit not active.
Message.Actions: Activate mechanical unit before defining test signals.

Message.Title: Overflow during logging
Message.Description: An overflow occurred when logging test signals or data log signals.
Message.Actions:
- Define fewer signals.
- Reduce load on main computer.
- Reduce network load.

Message.Title: No interrupts received
Message.Description: No interrupts received from the robot communication card within timeout.
Message.Consequences: The system goes to status SYS FAIL.
Message.Causes: The robot communication card may be faulty.
Message.Actions:
1) Restart the system to resume operation.
2) Replace the robot communication card if faulty.
3) Check any other error log messages coinciding in time with this one for clues.

Message.Title: Optimal Em. Stop change
Message.Description: Optimal Emergency Stop changed to Electrical brake mode because of acceleration limitation.
Message.Actions: Limit acceleration in the program.

Message.Title: Optimal Em. Stop change
Message.Description: Optimal Emergency Stop changed to Electrical brake mode because of torque limitation.
Message.Actions: Check load data.

Message.Title: Missing function
Message.Description: Absolute Accuracy not purchased.
Message.Actions: Change Robot system parameter Use Robot Calibration to uncalib.

Message.Title: Unsync due to CFG data
Message.Description:
- Mismatch between controller and cfg data for joint (calibration offset or calibration position), or
- Valid flags for calibration offset or commutation offset not true in cfg.
Message.Actions:
Update measurement system:
- Update revolution counter.
- Recalibrate joint.
- Change cfg data.

Message.Title: No acceleration limit
Message.Description: Acceleration limitation is not implemented for robot .

Message.Title: AbsAcc calibration failed
Message.Description: Could not perform an AbsAcc calibration.
Message.Actions:
- Restart controller.
- Check that the hard drive isn't full.
- Install more memory.

Message.Title: Command not allowed
Message.Description: Cannot set non motion execution mode when in MOTORS ON state.
Message.Actions: Change to MOTORS OFF.

Message.Title: Linked motor error
Message.Description: Large position offset between follower axis and master axis.
Message.Actions: Start linked motor service program. Jogg the follower axis to same position as the master axis.

Message.Title: Clear of Path failed
Message.Description: The movement has to be stopped when the path is to be cleared.
Message.Actions: Use StopMove before the ClearPath instruction. Move the program pointer and start a new movement.

Message.Title: Servo Tool error
Message.Description: Error for tool in state

Message.Title: Programmed force reduced
Message.Description: Programmed tip force too high for tool . Requested motor torque (Nm)= . Force was reduced to max motor torque.
Message.Actions:
1) Reduce programmed tip force.
2) Check force vs torque calibration in system parameters.
3) Check max motor torque in system parameters.

Message.Title: Calibration force reduced
Message.Description: Requested calibration force too high for tool . Requested motor torque (Nm)= . Force was reduced to max motor torque
Message.Actions:
1) Check calib forces in sys par.
2) Check force vs torque calibration in system parameters.
3) Check max motor torque in system parameters.

Message.Title: Tool opening failed
Message.Description: An ordered tool axis movement of was detected during tool opening.
Message.Actions: Make sure the tool opening is ready before executing next tool axis movement. Decrease the system parameter 'post sync time'.

Message.Title: Tool opening failed
Message.Description: An ordered tool axis movement of was detected during tool opening in calibration.
Message.Actions: Make sure no movements of the tool axis are ordered during calibration.

Message.Title: Cannot deactivate unit
Message.Description: Deactivation of mechanical unit may not be done while in process mode.
Message.Actions: Make sure to leave process mode before deactivating mechanical unit.

Message.Title: Linked motor error.
Message.Description: Too large speed for follower axis when follower axis is in jog mode.
Message.Actions: Start linked motor service program. Reset jog mode.

Message.Title: Sync pos warning
Message.Description: Sensor movement outside limits. The sensor start pos should be than and found .
Message.Actions: Check programmed sensor position in robtarget. Start sync earlier or change robtarget.

Message.Title: Sync speed warning
Message.Description: Programmed speed outside limits. The speed should be than and found .
Message.Actions:
- Check programmed robot speed
- Check sensor teach pos
- Check sensor nominal speed.

Message.Title: Sensor direction error
Message.Description: Programmed sensor pos speed and found sensor speed in opposite direction.
Message.Actions:
- Check programmed sensor positions in robtarget.
- Start sync earlier or reduce waitsensor dist .

Message.Title: Sensor max dist error
Message.Description: Distance between sensor position and programmed position too large.
Message.Actions:
- Check programmed sensor positions in robtarget.
- Check sensor speed.
- Start sync earlier or reduce waitsensor dist.

Message.Title: Sensor Check dist error
Message.Description: Distance sensor pos to programmed pos too large .
Message.Actions:
- Check programmed sensor positions in robtarget.
- Check sensor speed
- Increase max deviation.

Message.Title: WZone outside work area
Message.Description: The definition of minimum limit for the World Zone is outside work area for: ...
Message.Actions: Change the definition of the World Zone so the limit will be inside work area or insert 9E9 to remove an axis from test by the WZone.

Message.Title: WZone outside work area
Message.Description: The definition of maximum limit for the World Zone is outside work area for: ...
Message.Actions: Change the definition of the World Zone so the limit will be inside work area or insert 9E9 to remove an axis from test by the WZone.

Message.Title: Duty factor warning
Message.Description: The duty factor for the gearbox of joint of robot is too high. Continued running without adjustment may cause damage to motor and gearbox. Contact your local ABB service support center.
Message.Actions: Reduce the speed or increase the wait time.

Message.Title: Thickness out of reach
Message.Description: Servo Tool: Programmed thickness mm is out of reach
Message.Actions:
- Adjust programmed thickness
- Check working range (min. stroke)

Message.Title: Close request failed
Message.Description:
Not allowed to close Servo Tool: in reverse direction
Pre close position: mm
Programmed thickness: mm
Message.Actions:
- Adjust pre close position
- Adjust programmed thickness

Message.Title: Open request failed
Message.Description: Not allowed to open Servo Tool: in reverse direction
Message.Actions: Check that programmed robtarget positions of the Servo Tool are larger than programmed thickness.

Message.Title: Calibration failed
Message.Description: Not allowed to calibrate Servo Tool: from negative position
Message.Actions: Adjust Servo Tool position before calibration

Message.Title: Tune value out of limit
Message.Description: Tune value for Servo Tool: is out of limit. Parameter:
Message.Actions: Adjust tune value

Message.Title: Poor event accuracy
Message.Description:
Task:
The system is presently configured with time event supervision, and now an event could not be accurately activated.
Program Ref.
Message.Actions: Decrease the programmed speed or increase the distance between the programmed positions. Turn off this check by changing the system parameters.

Message.Title: Motion configuration

Message.Actions:
Check the configuration file.
I-start the system with correct parameters.
Check both configuration data for the current instance and any instances below in the structure.

Message.Title: Motion configuration
Message.Description: Incorrect configuration parameter for . The configuration parameter could for instance be an unknown type or a numerical value that is out of range.
Message.Actions:
Check the configuration file.
I-start the system with correct parameters.

I-start the system with correct parameters.

Message.Title: Motion configuration

Check the configuration file.
I-start the system with correct parameters.

Check the servo gun data in the configuration file.
I-start the system with correct parameters.

Message.Title: Motion configuration
Message.Description:
Servo tool change requires option Servo Tool Change.
Without this option, installation of this mechanical unit is not allowed.
